# Git author (GitHub)

This repository is hosted on **GitHub**. All commits must use:

- **Name:** zachlowes
- **Email:** zlowes@live.com

Do **not** use Softboat or softboat@proton.me here — that identity is reserved for GitLab repos.

When committing, set author via environment variables (do not change global git config):

```powershell
$env:GIT_AUTHOR_NAME='zachlowes'
$env:GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL='zlowes@live.com'
$env:GIT_COMMITTER_NAME='zachlowes'
$env:GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL='zlowes@live.com'
```

```bash
export GIT_AUTHOR_NAME='zachlowes'
export GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL='zlowes@live.com'
export GIT_COMMITTER_NAME='zachlowes'
export GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL='zlowes@live.com'
```

Or pass `--author="zachlowes <zlowes@live.com>"` on `git commit`.
